			<p><strong><span class="smallcaps">Jaed Muncharoen Coffin</span></strong> is the author of <em>A Chant to Soothe Wild Elephants</em>, which chronicles the time he spent as a Buddhist monk in his mother&rsquo;s native village in Thailand. His forthcoming book, <em>Roughhouse Friday</em>, is about the year he fought as the middleweight champion of a barroom boxing show in Juneau, Alaska. Since becoming a father, he has stopped having dangerous adventures in remote places. He lives with his wife and daughter in Portland, Maine.</p><a href="/contributors/jaed-muncharoen-coffin" class="block-contributor-link link-alt small">More From This Contributor&nbsp;&#9656;</a>		</div>
	</div>
</div>

							</footer>
						</article>


